text: Klaas Tuinstra (10 February 1945 â€“ 2 February 2022) was a Dutch politician. He was a member of the Anti-Revolutionary Party and later the Christian Democratic Appeal. He was a member of the Provincial States of Friesland from 1971 to 1986, a municipal councillor of het Bildt from 1974 to 1982, and an MP from 1986 to 1994. Tuinstra was born in Sint Annaparochie. He died in the same place on 2 February 2022 at the age of 76. ==References== Category:1945 births Category:2022 deaths Category:Anti-Revolutionary Party politicians Category:Christian Democratic Appeal politicians Category:Dutch Calvinists Category:Dutch councillors Category:Dutch provincial politicians Category:Members of the House of Representatives of the Netherlands Category:Politicians from Friesland
